{
  "_doc": "Magic: The Gathering | The Hobbit (code HOB) — Universes Beyond expansion, releases 2026-08-14. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-the-hobbit (odds extracted verbatim from the article text 2026-07-23, mid-preview — ~127 of the set's prints indexed on Scryfall). Lineup is Play Boosters + Collector Boosters only (Draft Night is a Play Booster event box; Scene Boxes / Bundles / Box Toppers are not modeled as packs), hence authoritative:true. MSRPs from the article: Play $6.99, Collector $37.99. Per-slot weight conversions follow msh.json's conventions: the three per-BOOSTER phrasings are divided across their slot group — common-slot scenes '7.8%' -> 7.8/7 = 1.1 per common slot, uncommon-slot scenes '5.5%' -> 5.5/3 = 1.8 and Dragon hoard '10.9%' -> 10.9/3 = 3.6 per uncommon slot, Collector uncommon-slot surge Dragon hoard 'In 1 of 10 Collector Boosters' -> (100/10)/4 = 2.5 per slot; sub-percentages reported as 'less than 1%' are entered as 0.5; the ~500-copy gleaming gold Smaug headliner is 0.1, mirroring spm.json's Soul Stone / msh.json's cosmic Mind Stone convention. Art-card slot: 'Art card (35%) or traditional foil double-sided token (65%)', '1 in 7 art cards gold stamped' -> 30 art / 5 stamped / 65 token. All hob_*/hoc_* filters are collector-number blocks derived from the article's image filenames + sheet censuses and cross-checked against the indexed pool — see _doc_hob in data/filters.json for the full CN map, the preview-era tagging caveats, and the REQUIRED post-release audit (~2026-08-14): re-census every block against the released pool exactly like msh.json's AUDIT 2026-07 #2 before trusting chase rates. The 'Middle-earth classic artist', 'Scene Box scene', and 'Dwarvish language' sheets live in the eternal-legal companion set HOC (Scryfall: The Hobbit Commander), not HOB — those outcomes reference set HOC directly. The Collector non-foil Booster Fun slot's 'mythic rare extended-art HOC card (5.3%)' block is not yet indexed, so that outcome uses the generic frame-based extended_art filter scoped to HOC — it matches nothing until Scryfall catalogues those prints, then self-corrects; pin its CN block during the audit. Seasonal Hobbit basics (#313-320, Bundle/Prerelease/Gift Bundle only) are deliberately reachable by NO outcome. Dwarvish outcomes' filter carries lang:'dw' so collectRecipeLanguages keeps Dwarvish prints in the client pool.",
